Viruses / Trojans to have a dropper must generally have an executable (exe, dll, or active file altering / renaming mechanism). Heuristic scanning may also see anything that reaches into another file as a type of malware (keygens). Stop using heuristic scanning if you don't want to pull out every keygen and related software. IF the datafile is up to date; a keygen that does function as a dropper will get tagged.

AVI files cannot be infected unless they are junk and are designed to be renamed as executable from another program (then you'd have a 700Mb dropper.....Unlikely!)

Most every file I have ever seen in p2p type sharing that really DOES have some malware is SO pathetic that if you can't knock it down, you need to learn. The only seriously respectable malware programs are those that "scan" your machine and funtion as a "blackmail" program. Those are genrally rather sofisticated & writen to actively work against anti-malware programs. DON'T EVER let yourself get "scanned" my websites claiming to make your machine run faster, clean out viruses or any other similar thing. Movies are safe: unless you are SO lame that you run some executable in the package for some reason. 
Just watch the movie.
